==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lachrymatory
<hw>Lach"ry*ma*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
-<plw>ries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>lacrymatoire</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A
⟦ldquo⟧tear-bottle;⟦rdquo⟧ a narrow-necked vessel found in sepulchers of
the ancient Romans; -- so called from a former notion that the tears of
the deceased person's friends were collected in it. Called also
<altname>lachrymal</altname> or <altname>lacrymal</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lachrymatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: lachrymatory
<hw>lachrymatory</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Relating to or inducing
tears; -- especially of chemical substances.</def>
<see>lacrimator</see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lacrimatory.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lachrymiform</ent>⟦br⟧
